🎯 Architecture Design

We have:

Frontend → Backend → Database
🧱 Kubernetes Design
1️⃣ Frontend

• Pod / Deployment
• Service (NodePort / LoadBalancer)

2️⃣ Backend API

• Pod / Deployment
• Service (ClusterIP)

3️⃣ Database

• StatefulSet (important)
• Persistent Volume
• Service (ClusterIP)

📦 Diagram
[ User ]
   ↓
[ Frontend Service ]  (LoadBalancer)
   ↓
[ Frontend Pods ]
   ↓
[ Backend Service ]  (ClusterIP)
   ↓
[ Backend Pods ]
   ↓
[ Database Service ]
   ↓
[ Database Pod (StatefulSet + Storage) ]
⚙️ Node Distribution

Example:

Node	Workload
Node 1	Frontend Pods
Node 2	Backend Pods
Node 3	Database
🔥 Production Notes

• DB NEVER in normal pod → use StatefulSet
• Use Secrets for DB password
• Use Ingress instead of NodePort (later topic)

🧠 Interview-Level Insight

If interviewer asks:

👉 “Why not run DB in Deployment?”

Answer:

• No stable identity
• No persistent storage guarantee
• Data loss risk
